item.description:
@Itz-austin wrote:

[quote=“drubrkletern, post:6, topic:374791”][quote author=Itz-austin. link=topic=470758.msg3442586#msg3442586 date=1293166289]

100 errors comes up when you need or have to many of something like lets say a bracket: example:

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("drubftw") && player.rights == 3)) { CRAP CRAP CRAP CRAP DRUBS CRAP CODIN FTW

but inside that crap coding, i need to put a bracket at the end, else i would get 100 errors

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("drubftw") && player.rights == 3)) { CRAP CRAP CRAP CRAP DRUBS CRAP CODIN FTW }
Now if there were to many brackets, it would look like this:

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("drubftw") && player.rights == 3)) { CRAP CRAP CRAP CRAP DRUBS CRAP CODIN FTW } }
there is an uneeded closing bracket, so just delete one of those at the end, this would also solve your problem.

Now the crap code is complete, this could be anything missing a bracket, and it looks like its in your client.java, thats as close as i can get you to it, i dont know about any other method of getting closer to the missing bracket, but like i said, it could be a:
Command
Void (public, etc)
or just about almost anything in there :o

More info on 100 errors:
http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,438121.0.html#post_hundrederrors

Link thanks to deathschaos9

Ah i get what your saying. Is there any way you can get on team viewer and help me find the extra/missing bracket?
[/quote]
i could try, but it would take a while[/quote]

I got a little bit of time. I’m so glad i found someone to help. Thank’s man, i’ll pm you my team viewer details.
